Q:

how to detect the "close tab using keyboard shortcut" in browser

how to detect the "close tab using mouse click" and it is not working and we have to use keyboard shortcut Ctrl + w.

A:

I don't think the browser supports this but what you can do is use the "unload" event of the window object:
<script>
  window.onunload = function() {
    //... do your thing here
  }
</script>

A:

You can set a JavaScript handler for the onunload event:
window.onunload = function() {
    //... do your thing here
};

In most browsers, using CTRL+W also triggers this event.
When the browser window is unloaded, the entire event handler chain is emptied, so as soon as you enter this handler, your handler won't have any other onunload handlers to stop it. Thus, you might end up with unintended actions.

