Is it possible to make a copy constructor that throws an error?

I want to overload my copy constructors to avoid writing my own copy constructor.  The way I've been thinking about the problem is to do something like this:
MyClass(const MyClass &) = delete;
MyClass(const MyClass &) throw(...);

