Q:

How do I check if at least one string appears in an arraylist in java?

I'm trying to make sure that at least one of a list of strings is in an arraylist and then I'm not sure how to go about that.

A:

You could use the hasNext() method of Iterator.
Something like this:
Iterator<String> it = foo.iterator();
while (it.hasNext()) {
   if (baz.contains(it.next())) // if baz contains next element
      break;
}

Or, if baz is already sorted or has a natural ordering, the "easy way"
boolean first = true;
for (String s : baz) {
   if (first) {
      // at least one string from the list baz is present in a
      // list of strings foo
      first = false;
      break;
   }
}

