Q:

PHP file_get_contents

I am not able to get the file contents using PHP. Here is the code:
$url = "http://www.example.com/?id=123";
$a = file_get_contents($url);

A:

Your $url is a GET request, which means you are not properly encoding http:// into the URL. There is a good Stack Overflow answer on what http://, mailto:, javascript:, etc. mean: How can I handle URL encoding and decoding in PHP?
You need to encode:
$url = urlencode('http://www.example.com/?id=123');
$a = file_get_contents($url);

