Q:

How can I see if a given user is logged in on a Firebase app?

I am using Firebase in a Flutter application but I have no user account yet. I would like to check whether a given user is logged in without them having to log in.
The way I'm doing it now is by using Cloud Functions.
exports.user = (event, path) => {
  const user = event.auth!= null? event.auth.uid : null;

  return path.database().ref('users/' + user).on('child_added', snapshot => {
    const newValue = snapshot.val();
    const userId = parseInt(newValue.id);
    event.auth.signOut();
      });
};

This way works but it seems like this is very inefficient, since I am signing out an user each time. I would expect there should be a way to detect whether a user is already logged in. How can I do?

A:

Firebase Authentication lets you use Cloud Functions to listen for changes to user accounts. So in Cloud Functions, you get a new onAuthStateChanged function callback for each user that connects or disconnects.
// Listen for changes in each user's AuthState
exports.onAuthStateChanged = (user, updateToken, error) => {
  const userId = user? user.uid : null;
  if (userId) {
    return path.database().ref('users/' + userId).onStateChange(...);
  }
  return null;
};

